<subSubSection pageId="200" pageNumber="478" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="200.[2068,2661,303,722]" pageId="200" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2069,2349,531,564]" pageId="200" pageNumber="478">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 105-158 mm, tail 80-110 mm, ear 15-17 mm, hindfoot 25-29 mm; weight 18-32 g. The Variable Grass Mouse is medium-sized species of 
<taxonomicName box="[2168,2267,693,722]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="200" pageNumber="478" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum is medium brown,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="200.[1455,2661,728,1194]" pageId="200" pageNumber="478">with dark-tipped underfur and black guard hairs; sides are paler; each eye has distinct pale eye-ring; chin is white or gray; venter and throat region are gray, with white to buffy tips; and dorsal surfaces of forefeet and hindfeet are whitish. Individual rump hairs are 11-13 mm long. Tail is relatively long, bicolored, and densely furred.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1456,2458,886,919]" pageId="200" pageNumber="478" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="200.[1455,2661,728,1194]" box="[1456,2458,886,919]" pageId="200" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1456,1568,886,919]" pageId="200" pageNumber="478">Habitat.</emphasis>
